ENTRY       EC 1.5.99.14                Enzyme
NAME        6-hydroxypseudooxynicotine dehydrogenase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
            With other acceptors
SYSNAME     1-(6-hydroxypyridin-3-yl)-4-(methylamino)butan-1-one:acceptor 6-oxidoreductase (hydroxylating)
REACTION    1-(6-hydroxypyridin-3-yl)-4-(methylamino)butan-1-one + acceptor + H2O = 1-(2,6-dihydroxypyridin-3-yl)-4-(methylamino)butan-1-one + reduced acceptor [RN:R07514]
ALL_REAC    R07514
SUBSTRATE   1-(6-hydroxypyridin-3-yl)-4-(methylamino)butan-1-one [CPD:C01297];
            acceptor [CPD:C00028];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     1-(2,6-dihydroxypyridin-3-yl)-4-(methylamino)butan-1-one [CPD:C15986];
            reduced acceptor [CPD:C00030]
COMMENT     Contains a cytidylyl molybdenum cofactor [3]. The enzyme, which participates in the nicotine degradation pathway, has been characterized from the soil bacterium Arthrobacter nicotinovorans [1,2].
